article.description: — Kane Williams had 21 points as Georgia State topped Georgia Southern 79-63 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Williams leads Georgia State over Georgia Southern 79-63
article.linkText: Williams leads Georgia State over Georgia Southern 79-63
article.story: ATLANTA -- — Kane Williams had 21 points as Georgia State topped Georgia Southern 79-63 on Thursday night. Corey Allen had 18 points for Georgia State (12-10, 6-5 Sun Belt Conference), which earned its fourth straight victory. Justin Roberts added 13 points and Eliel Nsoseme had 11 points and 11 rebounds. Williams shot 9 for 10 from the foul line. Kamari Brown had 17 points for the Eagles (11-13, 4-9), whose losing streak stretched to four games. Andrei Savrasov added 14 points and nine rebounds and Gedi Juozapaitis had 11 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
